<|startoftext|>Dish: mexican bean stir fry
Directions: in a dutch oven , heat the oil over medium heat
add in the carrots and onions
saute for 3-4 minutes until lightly browned
remove from the pan and set aside
add in the garlic and jalapeno peppers
saute for another 2-3 minutes just until the garlic sizzles
add in the beans to the pan
cook 1 minute over high , stirring frequently to not let them stick to the bottom of the pan
add in the broth all at once
stir to incorporate the broth , then deglaze with the reserved cooking liquid to make a thickish syrup
return the bean mixture to the pan
add in the diced jalapenos and stir a few minutes on high , reducing the heat a little
sprinkle in chopped green onions
season with salt and pepper to taste
serve and enjoy !'<|endoftext|>
<|startoftext|>Dish: mexican beef fajitas
Directions: in a bowl , combine the tomato , green onions , garlic , chili powder , cumin , cayenne , coriander , and salt
in a large heavy skillet , heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil
saut the beef in the olive oil until beginning to brown , then turn the beef in the skillet and add any juices that can accumulate in the skillet
meanwhile , in another skillet , heat the other tablespoon of olive oil
saute the beef in batches , turning once , until fully cooked , 3 to 4 minutes
toss the chopped green chile into the beef and cook until just beginning to brown on the outside , 1 to 2 minutes more
add the avocado , green onion , black pepper , chopped jalapeno pieces , salt , and cayenne to the beef , and stir to combine
